qas.question: In what city was Nasser raised?
What does Nasser's brother's name translate to?

context: Gamal Abdel Nasser was born on 15 January <a2_0>1918<a2_0/> in Bakos, Alexandria, the first son of Fahima and Abdel Nasser Hussein. Nasser's father was a <a0_0>postal worker<a0_0/> born in Beni Mur in Upper Egypt and raised in <a1_0>Alexandria<a1_0/>, and his mother's family came from Mallawi, el-Minya. His parents married in 1917, and later had <a4_0>two more boys<a4_0/>, Izz al-Arab and al-Leithi. Nasser's biographers Robert Stephens and Said Aburish wrote that Nasser's family believed strongly in the "Arab notion of glory", since the name of Nasser's brother, Izz al-Arab, translates to "<a3_0>Glory of the Arabs<a3_0/>"—a rare name in Egypt.
